## Scope

This slice adds EN/RU localization, which is net‑new (constraint 0.7): a
centralized, runtime‑read, human‑editable string resource (`strings.json`),
a `Localization.fs` loader with a startup completeness check and copyable
error surface, a persisted/restored language setting on
`EnvironmentSettings`, and language‑neutral scientific notation. It is
sequenced before the big UI slices so that the ribbon/menu/catalogue/control
text authored later resolves through `Localization.fs` from the start.

## Requirements

### R-1. Centralized, runtime‑read, editable resource (I.1)

I.1.1 A new module
`Berreman/OpticalConstructor/OpticalConstructor.Ui/Localization.fs` MUST
load all translatable string pairs from one centralized, human‑editable
text resource read at run time. The resource MUST be a JSON file
`Berreman/OpticalConstructor/OpticalConstructor.Ui/strings.json` holding,
per string key, the EN and RU values. An operator or translator MUST be
able to edit the strings, or add a further language, by editing that file —
no rebuild required (the file MUST be copied beside the assembly at build,
mirroring how the schema content item is shipped, SchemaValidation.fs:17,
and read from the runtime base directory).

### R-2. Language persisted and restored (I.2)

I.2.1 The selected language MUST be saved into settings and restored on the
next launch. `EnvironmentSettings` (UserEnvironment.fs:141) MUST be extended
with a `language` field, defaulting to English, and the environment schema
(`Berreman/OpticalConstructor/OpticalConstructor.Ui/optical-constructor-environment.schema.json`)
MUST be extended to match. The language selector MUST live on the *Settings*
ribbon (Part D) and MUST write through the existing save path
(UserEnvironment.fs:302).

### R-3. Startup completeness check with copyable error (I.3)

I.3.1 At startup the application MUST check the resource for completeness.
If any string is missing for the active language, the app MUST fall back to
the English default for that entry and MUST surface a startup error message
the user can **copy** (so it can be pasted into a bug report or a
translation fix), rather than failing silently or crashing. The startup
check and the copyable error surface MUST be wired in the app entry point
(`Berreman/OpticalConstructor/OpticalConstructor.App/Program.fs`).

### R-4. Language‑neutral scientific notation (I.4)

I.4.1 Scientific symbols and notation (Ψ, Δ, °, the unit symbols, R1/R2/R3)
MUST stay language‑neutral and MUST NOT be translated.

### R-5. Reuse before invention (I.5)

Reuse the `EnvironmentSettings` store (UserEnvironment.fs:141/:302) for the
saved language; reuse the build‑copied‑content‑item + base‑directory read
pattern (SchemaValidation.fs:17) for shipping and reading `strings.json`. Do
not introduce `.resx`/`ResourceManager` (constraint 0.7).

## Non-requirements

- No third language ships; the *mechanism* must support adding one by
  editing `strings.json`, but only EN and RU ship (0.6).
- No `.resx` / `ResourceManager` / `CultureInfo`‑based localization (0.7).
- The configurable **key map** fields on `EnvironmentSettings` / the
  environment schema are owned by slice 005 (Part E.8); this slice adds only
  the `language` field.
- The *Settings* ribbon control that hosts the language selector is wired in
  the Part D shell (slice 006); this slice provides the persisted setting and
  the selector's backing message path.
- The constructor‑as‑default‑landing edit to `Program.fs` is owned by slice
  006 (Part D.6); this slice adds only the startup completeness check and
  copyable error surface.

