## Risks

Medium: the `strings.json` build‑copy + base‑directory read must exactly
mirror the schema content‑item pattern (SchemaValidation.fs:17) or the
runtime read fails in the published layout; the startup completeness check
must surface a *copyable* error without crashing the headless smoke host.
Low risk on the `language` settings round‑trip (reuses the existing store).

## Hand-off

Record the `Localization.fs` public lookup API and the `language` field
shape on `EnvironmentSettings` so the Part D shell (slice 006) can place the
*Settings*‑ribbon language selector and so every later UI string resolves
through it. Note that `UserEnvironment.fs` / the environment schema still
need the **key‑map** extension (slice 005) and `Program.fs` still needs the
**default‑landing** edit (slice 006) — keep the `language` additions stable
for those follow‑on edits. Carry the `gates:` baseline YAML block forward.
